      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHmm, The problem is in destroy_pools():\n\ndestroy_pools () {\n        local fsname=${1:-$FSNAME}\n        local poolname\n        local listvar=${fsname}_CREATED_POOLS\n\n        [ x${!listvar} = x ] && return 0\n^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n\n        echo \"Destroy the created pools: ${!listvar}\"\n        for poolname in ${!listvar//,/ }; do\n^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n                destroy_pool $fsname.$poolname\n        done\n}\n\nI think we should fix the problem of destroy_pools by removing the usage of indirect variable expansion?\n\nWhat happended to the Shell of RHEL8. Changed from bash to another shell?\n\nI found following comment in the Internet:\n\nIf your shell doesn't support ${!...} then you'll have to use the eval hack.\nCode:\n\nVAR2=asdf\nVAR1=VAR2\neval echo \\$$VAR1",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d561a3f4dfbcef6d067e95e390e3d696c0cb81d0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 284,
        "name": "Emoly Liu",
        "email": "emoly@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "liuying_emoly"
      },
      "date": "2019-09-20 16:27:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThanks, Lixi. The key problem is that the special character in the indirect variable can't be valid anymore in newer version bash. I will try your way and see if it works.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "9e0bfdf68c5f2c317888602f1e8146b02aae67bf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 284,
        "name": "Emoly Liu",
        "email": "emoly@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "liuying_emoly"
      },
      "date": "2019-09-23 00:53:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nLixi, the method you mentioned works for the situation when ${!...} doesn't work, but our issue is, for your above example, VAR2 is not equal to asdf, but \"asdf,123\". The comma, the special character, is not valid in newer bash version.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
